					ovary subglobose, gradually narrowed at apex towards base of style;
					style 1.4 mm long, thick, split at base.

Fruit apocarpous, composed of 2 separate small mericarps;
					mericarps ellipsoid, 1.2-1.4 by 0.6-1 cm, apiculate at the apex, acumen very short;
					endocarps massive, hard, surrounding 2 lateral spongy cavities which are occupying the whole space at either side of the seed chamber.

