					petiole 1.5-6.6 cm long, glabrous;
					blades usually obovate, very rarely elliptic, 6.5-36 by 3.4-18 cm, ratio 1-3, base decurrent onto petiole, margin entire, apex often rounded or acuminate, sometimes retuse, shallowly retuse or truncate;
					secondary veins 21-42 pairs, straight to rather arcuate ascending, not reaching the margin, joining, forming a distinct submarginal vein which is close to the margin.

